OL,3,CWhy didn't Lindsay Hoyle chair the
OL,4,CBudget and who is the Deputy Speaker?
OL,6,FAs Rachel Reeves unveiled #40 billion
OL,7,Fworth of tax rises to "rebuild
OL,8,FBritain", it was Nusrat Ghani keeping
OL,9,Forder in the Commons instead of Sir
OL,10,FLindsay Hoyle.
OL,12,FSir Lindsay's absence at the Budget
OL,13,Fstatement is a matter of tradition.
OL,14,FUsually no Budget is led by the
OL,15,FSpeaker - instead it is left to a
OL,16,Fdeputy, the Chairman of Ways and Means.
OL,18,FThe position is currently occupied by
OL,19,FNusrat Ghani, who has served as Deputy
OL,20,FSpeaker of the House of Commons and as
OL,21,FChairman of Ways and Means since July.
