OL,3,CWhy didn't Lindsay Hoyle chair the
OL,4,CBudget and who is the Deputy Speaker?
OL,6,FThey had to represent the House's
OL,7,Finterests to the King on one hand, and
OL,8,Fthe King's interests to the House on
OL,9,Fthe other ` at times putting them at
OL,10,Fodds with both.
OL,12,FIn the late 17th century the Commons
OL,13,Fdecided that when it came to financial
OL,14,Fdemands from the King, it would need
OL,15,Fto resolve them as a whole house.
OL,17,FSo, the position of Chairman of Ways
OL,18,Fand Means was created, keeping the
OL,19,FSpeaker from chairing the budget who
OL,20,Fwas seen by some as the King's spy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
