OL,3,CWhy didn't Lindsay Hoyle chair the
OL,4,CBudget and who is the Deputy Speaker?
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FThe UK parliament website says: "It is
OL,12,Fthe custom for the Chairman to take
OL,13,Fthe chair during the debate on the
OL,14,FChancellor's Budget, even though there
OL,15,Fis nothing preventing the Speaker from
OL,16,Fpresiding over the Budget debate (and
OL,17,Fit has happened in practice). The
OL,18,Ffinancial measures contained in the
OL,19,FChancellor's Budget are brought in on
OL,20,FWays and Means Resolutions."
